metadata.name: Generations Bancorp NY Inc
metadata.description: Seneca-Cayuga Bancorp, Inc. operates as a bank holding company for Generations Bank that provides various banking products and services. The company's deposit products include statement, minor/custodian, money market, holiday club, school, and health savings accounts, as well as checking accounts and certificates of deposits. It offers mortgage loans, such as no closing cost, fixed rate, and adjustable rate mortgages, fixed and variable rate home equity line of credit, and home equity installment loans, as well as MyGenMortgage and federal housing administration loans; and consumer loans comprising personal, boat / RV / motorhome, snowmobile / jet ski / ATV / off-road motorcycle, construction, private and refinance student, and community hardship assistance loans, as well as generations overdraft line of credit. The company also provides auto, home, business, medicare, and life insurance services, as well as farm and agriculture insurance services. In addition, it offers securities and investment advisory services; and electronic and mobile banking services. The company was founded in 1870 and is headquartered in Seneca Falls, New York. Seneca-Cayuga Bancorp, Inc. is a subsidiary of Seneca Falls Savings Bank, MHC.
